{{Infobox stadium | name = Awadhesh Pratap Singh University Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Awadhesh Pratap Singh University Ground | former names = | location = [[Rewa, Madhya Pradesh]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1983 | built = | opened = 1983 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Awadhesh Pratap Singh University]] | operator = [[Awadhesh Pratap Singh University]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/58414.html Cricinfo] | publictransit = }} '''Awadhesh Pratap Singh University Stadium''' is a multi purpose stadium in [[Rewa, Madhya Pradesh]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket and other sports.<ref> [http://apsurewa.ac.in/Stadium.aspx Stadium]</ref> <ref> [http://apsurewa.ac.in/aboutunversity.aspx History of APS University, Rewa]</ref> The stadium has hosted a [[Ranji Trophy]] match <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1197_f.html First-class match]</ref> in 1970 when [[Madhya Pradesh cricket team]] played against [[Uttar Pradesh cricket team]] as match ended in drawn<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/44/44249.html Scorecard]</ref> but since then the stadium is regular of hosted non-first-class matches.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1197_misc.html Other matches]</ref>
