{{infobox country at games | NPC = BRA | NPCname = [[Brazilian Paralympic Committee]] | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1996 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.cpb.org.br }} | location = [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] | competitors = 60 (41 men and 19 women) | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 37 | gold = 2 | silver = 6 | bronze = 13 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1972 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
60 athletes (41 men and 19 women) from '''[[Brazil]]''' competed at the '''[[1996 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Atlanta]], [[United States]].<ref name="paralympic.org">{{Cite web|url=http://www.paralympic.org/Athletes/Results |title=Atlanta 1996 Paralympic Games: Brazil |accessdate=2012-08-27 |work=paralympic.org}}</ref>
