{{Infobox_Stadium | stadium_name = Dalton Convention Center | image = Northwest Georgia Trade and Convention Center, Dalton, Georgia.JPG | former_names = Northwest Georgia Trade and Convention Center | location = 2211 Dug Gap Battle RD., [[Dalton, Georgia|Dalton]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] 30720 | coordinates = {{Coord|34.75935|-85.00537|type:landmark_region:US-GA|display=title,inline}} | broke_ground = | opened = 1991 | closed = | demolished = | owner = City of Dalton and Whitfield County | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | tenants = [[Georgia Rampage]] ([[Xtreme Indoor Football League|XIFL]]) (2013–2015) | seating_capacity = 2,100 maximum capacity |}}
The '''Dalton Convention Center''' is a multi-purpose venue in [[Dalton, Georgia]] built in 1991. Owned by the city of Dalton and by [[Whitfield County, Georgia|Whitfield County]]. The Convention Center is operated by the general manager and director of tourism, Doug Phipps and Brett Huske.{{cn|date=November 2016}}
In addition to being home to the Georgia Athletic High School Coaches' Hall of Fame,<ref name="hshhf">{{cite web | url=http://www.nwgtcc.com/FacilityInformation/Amenities/GAHighSchoolCoachesHallofFame/tabid/667/Default.aspx | title=Georgia High School Coaches Hall of Fame | accessdate=2013-06-12}}</ref> the Convention Center's arena has a maximum seating capacity of 2,100 and was home to the [[Georgia Rampage]] of the [[Xtreme Indoor Football League]].<ref name="Rampage">{{cite web | url=http://daltondailycitizen.com/sports/x273851389/Called-to-the-carpet/print | title=Called to the carpet | publisher=Dalton Daily Citizen | date=2013-02-24 | accessdate=2013-06-12 | author=Golden, Devin}}</ref> Another [[Indoor American football|indoor football]] team, the [[Peach State Cats]], also announced the Dalton Convention Center as their home arena for the 2018 season, but became a traveling team and never played a home game in Dalton.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailycitizen.news/sports/local_sports/the-peach-state-cats-announce-move-to-dalton/article_c4a01382-0a62-52f4-a92e-cbf7deab65b4.html |title=The Peach State Cats announce move to Dalton |author=Tony Maluso |work=Daily Citizen News |date=November 1, 2017}}</ref>
