{{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio Muncipal de Lo Barnechea | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Lo Barnechea]], [[Santiago, Chile]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Municipality of [[Lo Barnechea]] | operator = | surface = grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 2,500 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = 105 x 68m | acreage = | tenants = [[Barnechea F.C.|Barnechea]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Estadio Municipal de Lo Barnechea''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Lo Barnechea]], [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]. It's [[Barnechea F.C.|Barnechea]]'s home stadium.
The stadium holds 2,500 people.
The first football match played in the played in the stadium was a 0–0 draw between [[Barnechea F.C.|Barnechea]] and [[Deportes Iberia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.24horas.cl/deportes/futbol-nacional/asi-es-el-nuevo-estadio-que-estrenara-barnechea--1909200|title=Así es el nuevo estadio que estrenará Barnechea|publisher=[[Televisión Nacional de Chile|24 Horas]]|language=Spanish|date=22 January 2016|accessdate=15 September 2018}}</ref>
