{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Father David Bauer Olympic Arena | nickname = | image = Father David Bauer Olympic Arena 2.jpg | location = 2424 University Dr NW, [[Calgary]], [[Alberta|AB]] T2N 3Y9 | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = 1963 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | owner = [[Calgary|City of Calgary]] | operator = | surface = Ice | construction_cost = | contractor = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Calgary Dinos]] ([[U Sports]]) (1963-present) [[Calgary Mustangs]] ([[Alberta Junior Hockey League|AJHL]]) (1990-present) | seating_capacity = 1,750 (seated, hockey) }} The '''Father David Bauer Olympic Arena''' is an [[ice hockey]] arena in [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], Canada. It seats about 1,750 for hockey with a standing room capacity of over 2,000. It is named after [[David Bauer (ice hockey)|Father David Bauer]], a [[Hockey Hall of Fame]]r and hockey pioneer.
Canada's defunct national touring team, the brainchild of Bauer, also staged tryouts there. The arena was built in 1963.<ref>http://www.calgary.ca/CSPS/Recreation/Pages/Arenas/Father-David-Bauer-and-Norma-Bush.aspx</ref>
The arena uses the {{convert|200|by|100|ft|m}} (or [[Olympics|Olympic]]) sized ice surface. A second arena, the ''Norma Bush Arena'' is attached to the facility, and has a {{convert|185|by|85|ft|m}} artificial ice surface.<ref name=city>{{Cite web|url= http://www.calgary.ca/CSPS/Recreation/Pages/Arenas/Father-David-Bauer-and-Norma-Bush.aspx | title= Father David Bauer / Norma Bush Arenas | author= City of Calgary |date=February 2007 | accessdate = 2011-09-16}}</ref>
The arena is the home of the [[Calgary Mustangs]] of the [[Alberta Junior Hockey League]] and the [[Calgary Dinos]] university hockey team. It is also the home of the [[Western Hockey League]] major junior circuit, the ''AAA Midget Flames'' of the [[Alberta Midget Hockey League]] and is often used as the training facility for the Canadian Olympic and junior national teams.<ref name=city/>
FDB also hosts games for the annual [[Mac's AAA midget hockey tournament]].
The arena was used for a few [[Ice hockey at the 1988 Winter Olympics|ice hockey]] games at the [[ice hockey at the 1988 Winter Olympics|1988 Winter Olympics]] as well as the compulsory figures section of the men's and women's figure skating competitions .<ref>[http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1988/orw1988pt1.pdf 1988 Winter Olympics.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110114080921/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1988/orw1988pt1.pdf |date=January 14, 2011 }} Part 1. pp. 186-9.</ref>
The arena is located in the same complex as [[McMahon Stadium]] and [[Foothills Stadium]], adjacent to the [[University of Calgary]].
