{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Koramangala Indoor Stadium | nickname = Multi Sports Complex | logo_image = | image = | caption = | Landscape = | location = [[Koramangala]], [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = 1997 | renovated = | owner = [[Government of Karnataka]] | operator = [[Government of Karnataka]] | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 2,000 }} '''Koramangala Indoor Stadium'''' is an indoor stadium in [[Koramangala]] area of [[Bangalore]] city in [[Karnataka]]. The stadium was built in 1997 to promote National games and indoor sports in the city. The stadium has a tennis court, an outdoor basketball court, a badminton court as well as a table tennis complex. The stadium is owned and managed by [[Government of Karnataka]]'s Ministry of Youth Empowerment and Sports.<ref>[http://www.karnatakayouthportal.in/?page_id=160 Ministry of Youth Empowerment and Sports]</ref>
The stadium is one of the stadiums that was used for the [[Pro Wrestling League]].<ref>[http://www.prowrestlingleague.com/ Pro Wrestling League]</ref> It is set to host the home matches of the [[Bengaluru Blasters]] in the [[Premier Badminton League]]'s 2017 season.<ref>http://www.pbl-india.com/teams/bengaluru-blasters/</ref> It is also used for non-sports activities like exhibitions, seminars and cultural activities.
