{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Use British English|date=April 2018}} A '''selector''' in [[cricket]] is a person given the administrative duty to choose the players that will represent a particular team in a match.<ref> Arya Sekhar Chakraborty. [https://www.sportskeeda.com/cricket/indian-national-selectors-roles-responsibilties Indian National Selectors: Roles and Responsibilities.] Sportskeeda.</ref>
There is typically heavy scrutiny on national team selectors, including those of the major [[Test cricket|Test]] cricketing nations like [[Australian national cricket team|Australia]], [[England national cricket team|England]], and [[India national cricket team|India]]. This is largely because in cricket, the highest level of the sport uniquely revolves around international competition,<ref> Devendra Pandey. [http://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/five-selectors-with-13-tests-between-them-bcci-3043120/ Five new India selectors with 13 Tests between them.] Indian Express.</ref> leaving national team selectors with a great deal of responsibility. Should the teams they select fail, the selectors are often vilified for the national side's poor performances.<ref>Jon Pierik. [http://www.smh.com.au/sport/cricket/who-will-be-australian-crickets-longterm-chairman-of-selectors-20161116-gsr1te.html Who will be Australian cricket's long-term chairman of selectors?] The Sydney Morning Herald.</ref>
